<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,260,284]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name, a combination of 
<emphasis box="[751,816,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">draco</emphasis>
, meaning dragon, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1084,1176,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nirvana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1176,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Nirvana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1236,1284,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
genus of the tribe in which the new genus is placed, refers to the dragonlike appearance of these insects and is treated as a feminine noun.
</paragraph>
